## Trade Review

- Referencing NY time, with 24-hour times in XM (GMT+2) (stating PNG time when applicable).
- At 10:30 PM PNG time, I marked out the 1200 H4 candle range.
- Got confused with the tutorial; adjusted it back, marking 8 AM as the last H1 candle, though 9 AM was actually the last H1 candle in the 1200 H4 range.
- Adjusted again and stuck with the 1200 H4 candle range, letting 9 AM play out as the last H1.
- Calculated ATR 4 x10 to be 60 pips for SL.
- Opened two positions at the 1630 M15 candle before the purge while watching M1:
  - 0.4 lot at 60 pips SL.
  - 0.2 lot at 120 pips SL.
- The 0.4 lot got stopped out, resulting in a loss of -$243.20.
- Price broke the CRT low with a proper M5 TS at 1650, which also stopped me out of the first position.
- Waited for a pullback on M1 at 61.8 Fibo level but hesitated to enter (this was an unplanned entry).
- Took an entry after confirmed upward movement at 1717 M1 candle with 0.2 lots, setting SL at 60 pips (also unplanned and added risk).
- Adjusted TP levels: 
  - One at 75% above the dollar amount of the losing trade ($243).
  - The other set at 100%.
- Moved both SLs to BE + $10.
- During the 1745 M15 retracement, panicked and secured one TP at $109, ensuring I remained above starting equity.
- Held the other trade until morning, closing around 9 AM PNG time.
- As of 3 PM PNG time, Gold price is around 95% of yesterday's CRT range.

---

## Successes

- $100 profit overall.
- CRT + TS success up to the 95% range.

## Failures & Solutions

1. Confused candle ranges:
   - Solution: Stick to the 1200 H4 range consistently.
   
2. Early entry before true TS:
   - Solution: Wait for the M5 TS at CRT low/high before entering.
   
3. Stopped out at 60 pips:
   - Solution: Increase SL1 to ATR x 15 and keep SL2 at ATR x 20.
   
4. Loss larger than TP:
   - Solution: Adjust lot size for larger SL or make SL2 lot size larger than SL1 to let smaller positions get stopped out in volatility.
   
5. Didn't hold position to CRH:
   - Solution: Move SL significantly to BE + 50% and hold the second position. Since we're testing CRT, see it through.
   
6. Didn't emphasize daily bias:
   - Solution: Always trade with the bias. If H4 is a retracement, take the reversal. If H4 is a continuation, CRT may fail, so use strong SLs or avoid going against the trend.
